rest_of_day_open: I see it being busy and medium stress. I have a lot to accomplish and my husband is counting on me to finish my tasks. At the same time, I will be doing a lot of things I find enjoyable: cooking with my husband, playing games with family online, decorating for christmas, and finally having a tidy home.
critical_positive: My partner was amiable toward the various topics I brought up. He was willing to share information about his personal life. We had a couple things in common. He found one of my stories interesting and had some encouraging words about my job as a music teacher. He was pleasant and friendly.
critical_negative: I believe that affirmation and empathy is important and I don't think he offered much of either.  Our point of views differed on how we respect science in regards to COVID and quarantine. That's an important subject to me as it indicates whether a person values his community and the people directly around them.

rest_of_day_open: I think it will go well. I look forward to spending time with my family. We go on errands together and go out and have fun. We also like to go out and explore and also eat out at take out restaurants. It should be exciting to see how the week plays out.
critical_positive: Christa was extremely friendly and always smiling. So it was very inviting to talk and exchange with her. We went back and forth with questions, if there was a little space she would jump in and ask a question. We had many opportunities to to talk about many subjects; it was great!
critical_negative: Nothing really went poorly. There were minimal pauses, but it was not but a literal few seconds until one of us jumped in and talked. We both were interested in each others life enough to keep on speaking. She also is having a negative experience with the covid which is quite different than our experience, so that could have gone wrong but it did not.
